  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0bae\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1 \u0b85\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9a\u0ba9\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b89\u0bb0\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc2\u0bb2\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bae\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bae\u0ba9\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bc6\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bc6\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc1 - \u0b85\u0b9c\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbf \u0baa\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bbe",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "President cannot win people's hearts by addressing them from the floor of Parliament - Ajit B Perera",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "President Ranil Wickremesinghe has ended the session of the Parliament to show the people that he is the President of the country by giving an aggressive speech in the Parliament.",
        "Ajit P Perera, member of United People's Shakti Political Council, said that you cannot win the hearts of the people by addressing them from the seat of aggression.",
        "President Ranil Wickremesinghe said this while participating in a press conference held by President Ranil Wickremesinghe regarding the termination of the parliamentary session.",
        "Ranil Wickramasinghe, who has been elected by the Parliament as the Interim President, is currently concluding the session of the Parliament.",
        "When a new president is appointed in the country, it is normal for him to formally open the parliament and deliver a policy declaration speech from the Speaker's seat.",
        "But the current President Ranil Wickramasinghe came to the Parliament as the Executive President and addressed the people in the Royal Sadai and ended the session of the Parliament to show the people that he is the President of this country.",
        "But the problem is that the president must be in the hearts of the people. The President cannot win the hearts of the people by addressing the parliament from the throne.",
        "Also, the country can be managed by the President who can fulfill the expectations of the people.",
        "Only such a person can explain to the people of the country. Otherwise, a president who was elected as the interim president through funds and votes obtained through the parliamentary deal, cannot win the hearts of the people, no matter how many ceremonies are held at the end of the session of the parliament, even if he delivers a campaign speech. We are worried about this, he said."
      ],
